From 81d176d7fbc52de346419a737327a2ca9ae2ae67 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 23:43:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat: SaaS multi-tenancy, self-serve auth, and keyed
 snippet (Phases 1-3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 1 — Multi-tenant architecture:
- Add Organization model with publicKey, slug, plan fields
- Add OrganizationMember join table with OrgRole enum
- Add passwordHash, emailVerified, verification/reset token fields to User
- Scope Test, Integration, FrictionSignal, Hypothesis, AuditLog to organizationId
- Update all API routes and server pages to filter by session.orgId
- Update AI engine and friction detector to query by org instead of user

Phase 2 — Self-serve auth:
- JWT session auth (jose, httpOnly cookie, 30-day expiry)
- Password hashing via Node.js built-in crypto.scrypt
- POST /api/auth/signup — creates user + org + owner membership
- POST /api/auth/signin — email/password login
- POST /api/auth/signout — clears session cookie
- GET  /api/auth/me — returns current user + org
- GET  /api/auth/verify-email — token-based email verification
- POST /api/auth/forgot-password — generates reset token (logs in dev)
- POST /api/auth/reset-password — consumes token, sets new password
- Next.js middleware protecting all dashboard/API routes
- Login page wired up with error handling and redirect
- Signup page with password min-length validation
- 3-step onboarding wizard (workspace name → snippet install → done)
- Forgot password + reset password pages
- DashboardLayout shows real user info and functional sign-out
- PATCH /api/org — rename workspace (owner/admin only)

Phase 3 — Keyed snippet:
- Snippet uses data-key="pk_xxx" attribute instead of data-store-id
- /api/snippet/tests looks up org by publicKey (no auth required, CORS open)
- /api/snippet/events accepts key field alongside legacy storeId
- Settings → Snippet page shows public key + copy-paste install code
- Install guides for Shopify, generic HTML, and Next.js

